# General Development Guidelines

## Senior Developer Standards
- Approach all tasks with a senior developer's perspective
- Consider edge cases and potential failure points
- Review and refactor code for optimal performance and maintainability
- Document architectural decisions and their rationale

## Documentation Requirements
- Include references to all external resources used (documentation, articles, libraries)
- Document any assumptions made during implementation
- Add JSDoc/TSDoc comments for all functions and classes
- Maintain a changelog for significant changes

## Code Quality Standards
- Prioritize code accuracy over development speed
- Write comprehensive error handling
- Include type definitions and validations
- Write self-documenting code with clear variable and function names

## Development Process
- Always include 'use context7' in prompts for consistent development
- Document the intent and reasoning behind code changes
- Preserve existing code as comments when making modifications
- Add TODO comments for future improvements or technical debt

## Maintainability Guidelines
- Follow SOLID principles
- Keep functions small and focused
- Use dependency injection where appropriate
- Implement proper separation of concerns
- Write modular and reusable code

## Version Control
- Write clear and descriptive commit messages
- Reference related issues or documentation in commits
- Keep commits focused and atomic
- Review changes before committing
